# Git LFS Configuration Examples
# These files are typically large and should be handled by Git LFS if committed.
# By default, our .gitignore prevents these from being committed to keep the repo light.
# If you intentionally want to track these in the repository, uncomment the lines below
# and ensure you have git-lfs installed (https://git-lfs.github.com/).

# *.mp4 filter=lfs diff=lfs merge=lfs -text
# *.mov filter=lfs diff=lfs merge=lfs -text
# *.wav filter=lfs diff=lfs merge=lfs -text
# *.png filter=lfs diff=lfs merge=lfs -text
# *.jpg filter=lfs diff=lfs merge=lfs -text
# *.jpeg filter=lfs diff=lfs merge=lfs -text
# *.safetensors filter=lfs diff=lfs merge=lfs -text
